## When to use this skill

Use for **StoreOS ↔ WooCommerce sync**: incoming **`/wp-json/oc-storeos/v1/orders`**, **`/default-closing-dates`**, **outgoing order POST** on configurable status, **OrderPayment v2** webhooks (`woocommerce_payment_complete`, order **completed**), **admin options** (`oc_storeos_integration_options`), order meta **`_oc_storeos_*`**, **percentage cart fee**, or **formatted address** overrides for StoreOS-originated orders.

## Core files

- `wp-content/plugins/oc-storeos-integration/oc-storeos-integration.php` — defines `OC_STOREOS_INTEGRATION_VERSION`, `OC_STOREOS_INTEGRATION_PLUGIN_DIR`, **`OC_StoreOS_Integration_Updater`** (GitHub updates, `PLUGIN_BASENAME` `oc-storeos-integration/oc-storeos-integration.php`), loads the main class; boots **`OC_StoreOS_Integration::get_instance()`** on `plugins_loaded` only if **`class_exists( 'WooCommerce' )`**.
- `wp-content/plugins/oc-storeos-integration/includes/class-oc-storeos-integration.php` — entire integration: constants `OPTION_NAME` (`oc_storeos_integration_options`), meta keys `META_SYNCED` (`_oc_storeos_synced`), `META_LAST_ERR`, `META_LAST_SYNC`, `_oc_storeos_external_order_id`, gateway `GATEWAY_CARDCOM` (`cardcom`), Cardcom meta label `META_CARDCOM_PAYMENT_ID` (`Cardcom Payment ID`), dedup transients `TRANSIENT_OUT_ORDER_HASH_PREFIX` / `OUT_ORDER_DEDUP_TTL`, `PAYMENT_METHOD_SEND_ORDER_STATUS_OFF` (`__oc_storeos_send_order_off__`), REST log under uploads `REST_INCOMING_LOG_DIR` / `REST_INCOMING_LOG_FILE`.

## Main flows

- **REST (incoming):** `register_rest_routes` — namespace **`oc-storeos/v1`**, routes **`/orders`** (`POST` → `rest_create_order`, **`permission_callback` = `__return_true`**) and **`/default-closing-dates`** (`POST` → `rest_update_default_closing_dates`). Incoming orders logged via `log_rest_incoming_order` / `log_rest_orders_pre_dispatch` on `rest_pre_dispatch`. `rest_create_order` resolves existing order by `order_id` / `orderId` / `orderNumber`, maps `shippingAddress`, line items by **SKU or product id**, may call **`ocws_save_full_address_to_order( $order )`** when OCWS exists, sets **`_oc_storeos_external_order_id`** from payload, etc.
- **Outgoing Order sync:** `woocommerce_order_status_changed` → `handle_order_status_for_storeos_outgoing` (priority **20**) compares **`$new_status`** to `get_effective_send_order_to_storeos_status_for_order( $order )`; then `send_outgoing_when_order_enters` → `send_order_to_storeos` builds payload, dedupes with transient + `META_SYNCED`, POSTs via `send_order_to_api` (requires `api_base_url` + `api_token` in options).
- **OrderPayment v2:** `woocommerce_payment_complete` → `handle_payment_complete_webhook_v2` (priority **99**) and `woocommerce_order_status_changed` → `handle_order_completed_payment_webhook_v2` (priority **99**) when `completed`; gated by option **`send_order_payment_webhook_on_charge`**; uses `maybe_send_order_payment_webhook_v2` and re-entrancy guard `$payment_webhook_v2_dispatching`; Cardcom-only payload in `build_order_payment_webhook_v2_payload`.
- **Closing dates API:** `rest_update_default_closing_dates` writes Woo options (e.g. OCWS **`ocws_default_closing_dates`** / **`ocws_lp_default_closing_dates`**) via `resolve_default_closing_dates_option`; may use **`ocws_dates_array_to_string`** if defined.
- **Cart fee:** `woocommerce_cart_calculate_fees` → `add_order_percentage_fee` (priority **20**) — percent from **`order_total_fee_percent`** on subtotal + shipping; label from **`order_total_fee_cart_text`** or default “תוספת משקל”; tooltip HTML class **`oc-storeos-fee-tooltip`**; styles in `render_fee_tooltip_styles` on `wp_head`.
- **Admin UI:** `admin_menu` / `admin_init` — settings under `OPTION_GROUP` / `OPTION_NAME`; includes per-method **send order to StoreOS** mapping and **`oc_storeos_available_payment_methods_for_mapping`** filter.
- **Address display:** `woocommerce_order_get_formatted_billing_address` / `woocommerce_order_get_formatted_shipping_address` — only when **`_oc_storeos_external_order_id`** is set.

## Common mistakes - DO NOT

- **אבטחת REST:** המסלולים רשומים עם **`permission_callback` => `__return_true`** — אל תניח אימות מובנה; כל שינוי חייב להתחשב בהגנות ברמת רשת/שכבה חיצונית או הרחבה מכוונת.
- אל תשלח הזמנה יוצאת פעמיים באותו payload — יש **transient dedup** (`TRANSIENT_OUT_ORDER_HASH_PREFIX`) ו־**`META_SYNCED`**; לפני debug נקה מטא/טרנסיינט במודעות.
- אל תבלבל בין **סנכרון הזמנה מלא (Order)** לבין **OrderPayment v2** — אופציות נפרדות (`send_order_to_storeos_status` לעומת `send_order_payment_webhook_on_charge`).
- שינוי סטטוס טריגר: `get_effective_send_order_to_storeos_status_for_order` יכול להחזיר **`PAYMENT_METHOD_SEND_ORDER_STATUS_OFF`** לשער ספציפי — לא לדרוס בלי להבין מפת שערים.
- שימוש ב-**`send_outgoing_when_order_enters`** עם `skip_status_gate` רק כשמבינים את ה-implication (echo מ-REST וכדומה).

